The Commonwealth of Kentucky War of 1812 Bicentennial Commission shall be composed of eighteen (18) members, as follows:
Two (2) members of the Kentucky House of Representatives, appointed by the Speaker of the House of Representatives;
Two (2) members of the Kentucky Senate, appointed by the President of the Kentucky Senate;
The adjutant general or the adjutant general's designee;
The secretary of the Education and Workforce Development Cabinet or the secretary's designee;
The secretary of the Tourism, Arts and Heritage Cabinet or the secretary's designee;
Two (2) members from the Kentucky Historical Society, appointed by the executive director of that agency;
Three (3) members from the Kentucky Heritage Council, appointed by the executive director of that agency, including at least one (1) member each from the Kentucky African-American Heritage Commission and the Kentucky Native American Heritage Commission;
One (1) member from the Kentucky Humanities Council, appointed by the executive director of that agency; and
Five (5) citizen members from the state at large with a demonstrated interest in history and substantial knowledge and appreciation of the War of 1812, appointed by the Governor.
